@model openSPM.Model.AppModel

@section StyleSheets{
    <style>
        img.image-wrap {
            float: left;
            margin: 0 15px 5px 0;
            vertical-align: central;
        }

        p.image-wrap {
            text-align: justify;
        }

        ul.image-wrap {
            list-style-position: inside;
        }

        div {
            margin-top: 0em;
            margin-bottom: 1em;
        }
    </style>
}

<table class="table table-striped">



    <colgroup>
        <col class="col-md-12">
    </colgroup>

    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Step&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Description</td>
        </tr>
        <tr valign="middle">
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/1settings.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>By clicking on "settings" in the main menu, those with authorization can Users, Products and Business Unit Information</div>
                    <ul class="image-wrap small">

                        <ul>
                            <li><u>Administrator</u>, the IT Professionals responsible for the system
                            <li><u>Owner</u>, (or Process Owner), the individuals responsible for assuring corporate CIP-007-R2 compliance
                            <li><u>BUC</u>, Business Unit Coordinator, the approval authority for Mitigation Plans
                            <li><u>PIC</u>, Patch Input Coordinator, those responsible for maintaining configuration of openSPM, especially the Products List
                            <li><u>SME</u>, Subject Matter Expert, the individuals in each BU that are responsible for discovering, assessing, installing (or overseeing installation) patches and for developing mitigation plans.
                            <li><u>Viewer</u>, users with read-only assess to openSPM
                        </ul>
                        <br />

                        <li>
                            The <b>Product List</b> This is the list of assets where CIP-007-R2 is applicable.  This list is maintain by PICs -- an openSPM CCA list adminstrator.
                            Each SME is associated with one or more products.
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            The <b>Business Unit</b> (BU) List.  Business units represent the logical grouping of SMEs into an approval authority or Business Unit Coordinator.
                            Both a primary and alternate Business Unit approval authority can be designated for each BU.
                            Owners can create as many business units as necessary to manage BU Coordinator to SME accountability relationships.
                        </li>


                    </ul>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr valign="middle">
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/2check.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of products (CCA) on which the availablity of security patches much be checked.</b>
                    </div>

                    <div>

                        <div>
                            From time-to-time (typically weekly) SMEs will review each patch source in openSPM and document that these sources have been
                            checked for new patch availability. OpenSPM will log the time that this source/vendor was checked and the outcome of this discovery
                            by clicking on the "Record" button. The SME can optionally attach documents that might be useful to either:
                            (1) assist in the documentation of compliance or (2) be of value in the creation of "candidate security patches".
                        </div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr valign="middle">
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/3new.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of patches where an assessment is pending.</b>  The patch information can be edited from this screen.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        As new candidate security patches are discovered in Step 2, the SME adds (copy and pastes from the vendor's product web site)
                        these to openSPM by clicking on the "Add New" button.  The minimum required information for entry of a new patch the patch title.
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        The SME is asked to confirm the start date for compliance timers as part of this process.  The SME will work
                        with the Owner to assign an appropriate start date if using the compliance default start of the “vendor release date” does not allow sufficient time for patch
                        assessment prior to expiration of the 35-day assessment period.
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        As much information as is available from the vendor should be added to define the patch.  Fields are provided in the openSPM patch
                        entry from for this additional information.  Documents, such as PDFs, can be attached if they available from the vendor.
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        A "Patch Availability Notification" (PAN) number is assigned by the system and the patch "explodes"
                        to each BU as shown in the process diagram below.   Patch Tracking now begins for each BU for this PAN.
                    </div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/4assess.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of patches where an assessment is pending </b> filtered by Business Unit.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            Each BU has 35 days (typically from the vendor's patch release date) to "assess" the patch.  This assessment can be
                            performed by any SME in the BU which is associated with one of the Products linked to the patch.
                            If multiple SMEs within a BU have been associated with the Product, then all these SMEs have permission to represent the BU in the assessment
                            of the patch.  Only one assessment is allowed per patch per BU.
                        </div>

                        <div> The minimum required information that must be entered as part of the assessment is one of four “Assessment Results”:</div>
                        <ul class="image-wrap small">
                            <li>The patch is applicable -- Install the patch</li>
                            <li>The patch is applicable -- Develop a mitigation plan (which can include patching some, but not all, devices)</li>
                            <li>The patch is NOT applicable -- the patch does not apply to my BU's configuration
                            <li>The patch is NOT an applicable -- the patch is not security related for my BU</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div>
                            If the assessment results in decision to develop a mitigation plan, the SME should enter the "Assessment Basis".

                            Completing the assessment starts a new 35-day timer for this business unit for the action of (1) installing the patch
                            or (2) developing a mitigation plan.
                            Notifications will be sent to the BU Coordinator and SMEs in this Business Unit (as well as the Owner) as the 35-day compliance date approaches.
                        </div>

                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/5install.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of patches where installation (applicaiton of the patch) is pending.</b>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            Once the patch has been installed on all CCA within the BU, an SME for the Product in the impacted BU must enter the “patch installation
                            completion” date in openSPM. The SME should also enter notes and/or attach documents that provide details and evidence of the installation.
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            By clicking on the "Reassess" button, the SME can change the outcome of the assessment from "Patch" to other assessment options.  Changing the assessment conclusion
                            does not change the compliance-based date of when the orginial assessment was completed.
                        </div>


                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/6plan.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of patches where development of a mitigation plan is pending.</b>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            If an assessment calls for a mitigation plan, a "Mitgation Plan Form" is completed by the SME, approved by the BU Coordinator, and
                            emailed to the PIC for review and entry into the openSPM system.
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            By clicking on the "Reassess" button, the PIC can change the outcome of the assessment from "Develop Mitigation Plan" to other assessment options.  Changing the assessment conclusion
                            does not change the compliance-based date of when the orginial assessment was completed.
                        </div>

                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/7updateplans.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays the list of open mitigation plans.</b>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            After mitgation plans have been loaded into openSPM by the PIC in Step 6, the PIC must close these plans once they are completed and may update the mitigation plans as needed.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <img src="~/Images/ProcessSteps/Small/8history.png" class="image-wrap" />
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div>
                        <b>Displays historical data.</b>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            After patches are complete, they show up here. All important dates are recorded and can be used as proof of compliance. Records can be exported to a csv file.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div><a id="Definitions"></a>Definitions:</div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Business Unit</b> (BU) - Business units represent the logical grouping of SMEs.  A "BU" is an organizational entity (real or virtual) that has
                        a coordinator (the approval authority) and SMEs (the technical experts) that have responsibility for CCA contained in openSPM's Product List
                    </div>
                    <div><b>Candidate Security Patch</b> - These are the patches that SMEs discover that may have security implications to CCA. </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Patch Assessment</b>- Assessments are a compliance requirement and are conducted by SMEs to determine if a candidate patch
                        is an applicable security patch and if so the action required to address it -- either patch or mitigate.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Patch Assessment Notification Number</b> (PAN #)- Following patch assessment, if a candidate securtity patch is applicable a "PAN #" is assigned by the
                        openSPM system so that fucture action for this patch for each BU can be tracked.  (PAN # is also referred to as "Patch ID".)
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Mitigation</b> - Actions taken to minimize risk without complete elimination of a specific vulnerability (e.g. implementing
                        additional process checks, adding access control mechanisms, authoring Intrusion Detection System rules to detect anomalous activities)
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <b>Patch Mitigation Plan</b> - The combination of risk assessment and justification for mitigation vs. patching PLUS a set of
                        action steps that will mitigate the need to install the patch.  The Mitigation Plan is stored in openSPM as an attached document.
                    </div>
                </p>
            </td>

        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div><a id="Evidence"></a>Evidence of Compliance:</div>
                    <div><b>Process Documentation</b> - TVA Transmission SPP 12.006, this help file and the functionality of openSPM.</div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Discovery Status Report </b> - f(Product) - min, max, & average Product "check" durations.  Patch release dates vs. check date (min, max, & avg).
                        Violation if check > 35 days from vendor release date.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Assessment Duration and Result Report</b> - f(Product), f(BU) - 35 day assessment period measured from the vendor's patch release date for this product.
                        Violation if all BUs have not assessed an applicable patch.  Results in openSPM provide evidence of assessments.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Patch Installation Duration</b> - f(Patch), f(BU) - min, max, & average by platform for each BU.
                        Violation if all BUs have not patched within 35 days.
                    </div>
                    <div><b>Patch Installation Evidence</b> - f(Patch), f(BU) - installation notes, attached documents</div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Mitigation Plan Development Duration</b> - f(Patch), f(BU) min, max, & average for each BU.
                        Violation if all BUs have not developed a plan within 35 days.
                    </div>
                    <div><b>Mitigation Plan Content</b> - f(Plan) - attached copies of the plan summary form.</div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div><a id="Roles"></a>User Roles:</div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Business Unit Coordinator</b> (BU Coordinator) - The individual with approval authority for a business unit's
                        security actions for CCA for which that BU is accountable.  A BU Coordinator opversees the patch assessment for
                        that business unit.  A BU Coordinator approves Mitigation Plans for their Business Unit.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Patch Input Coordinator</b> (PIC) - The openSPM process administrators responsible for maintaining openSPM configuration -- the applicable Product List and the association of Products to Business Units
                        and SMEs -- and for entering Mitgation Plans into openSPM.

                        <!-- The individuals responsible for (1) reviewing sources of patch availability,
                        (2) entering candidate security patches into openSPM for assessment by SMEs, and (3) closing patches that been successfully assessed / addressed by the BUs. -->
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Owner</b> (Security Patch Compliance Authority) - The corporate owner of the processes managed by openSPM.
                        The Owner can set business process configuration parameters and has full functionality on all system pages except for those pages reserved for Admins.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>Subject Matter Expert</b> (SME)- Professional staff within the business unit charged with discovering patches; making assessments
                        on the security applicability and methods; and for developing mitigation plans.
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <b>System Administrator</b> (Admin) - Information Technology personnel authorized to establish users and roles and
                        set implementation specific configuration parameters (e.g., data base location).  Admins have unrestricted access to all pages in the openSPM System.
                    </div>
                    <div><b>Viewer</b> - Those authenticated to the domain can view the status of active patches but cannot make any changes within the system. </div>
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p class="image-wrap">
                    <div><a id="Overview"></a>Process Overview:</div>
                    <img src="~/Images/patchexplosion3-framed.png" width="900" class="image-wrap" />
                </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="height: 150px; border: none">
            <td colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>

</table>
